9
00:00:39,914 --> 00:00:41,958
{\an8}<i>Is there an advisable way to break up?</i>

10
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,253
I think that's an important discussion.

11
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:47,630
Breakups are more important
than relationships.

12
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,759
A healthy breakup leads
to another healthy relationship,

13
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:54,220
and in a healthy relationship,
people can find love again.

14
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:57,098
Who's talking such nonsense?

15
00:00:58,558 --> 00:00:59,726
That was the question.

16
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,979
I was just giving my professional opinion.

17
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:06,357
What is a healthy breakup?

18
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,777
That's what I was talking about.

19
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:11,654
Step one. Inform your loved one
why you're breaking up.

20
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,823
You're an idiot.

21
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,825
Do you think they will understand why?

22
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:18,620
Even if they don't,
you should still tell them.

23
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:21,247
Step two. Break up face-to-face,

24
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,124
not via text or over the phone.

25
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:25,043
Do it in person and peacefully.

26
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:26,169
Why did you hit him?

27
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,800
-I broke up with her.
-That's not the whole story.

28
00:01:31,883 --> 00:01:33,218
<i>I believe we should tell</i>

29
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:36,179
the people we used to love
why we want to break up.

30
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:38,515
You said you couldn't stop
looking at my nostrils,

31
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:41,392
and it felt like
you were talking to my nostrils!

32
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:44,687
-<i>What they do next is up to them.</i>
-"She was offended.

33
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,397
He could only see her nostrils

34
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,525
whenever he looked at her."

35
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:51,903
Why did you say such mean things?

36
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:54,155
You could've been nice about it.

37
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,990
I was nice about it.

38
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:59,160
But when I kept giving her good excuses,
she didn't understand it.

39
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:02,413
See? Breakups can never be healthy.

40
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,291
You're ending a relationship
with someone you loved so dearly.

41
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:08,086
A breakup is inevitably painful
for everyone

42
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:10,004
regardless of who's ending it.

43
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,089
Yes.

44
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:12,674
It's painful however you put it.

45
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:15,343
You just have to move on with the pain.

46
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:37,866
I didn't get any sleep last night.

47
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:40,910
I lay down to get some sleep.

48
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:44,205
But I kept getting pissed off!

49
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,751
<i>Yes. That's it.</i>

50
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:52,130
You should get mad at her
and vow to take revenge.

51
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:55,049
No. Taking revenge makes no sense.

52
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:57,844
<i>Breakups are out of your hands,</i>

53
00:02:57,927 --> 00:02:59,888
<i>and so is the pain from breakups.</i>

54
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:02,015
<i>But I believe ruining your life</i>

55
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:05,977
