247
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:54,768
Eun-o went down to Busan last year.

248
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:57,521
And the woman was already pregnant
with the baby then.

249
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:01,734
Then, he was cheating on her.

250
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:03,569
-Yes.
-Is he still in Busan?

251
00:15:03,652 --> 00:15:05,487
-Let's take the train to Busan.
-Hey.

252
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:08,365
Kyeong-jun already beat him up.
I poured coke on him, too.

253
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:09,283
Sit down.

254
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:17,583
-That's why they broke up.
-That's why she vanished for three months.

255
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,502
He made her go to Busan
so they could be together.

256
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:24,214
They stayed together in Busan.
Once he got transferred to Seoul,

257
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:27,593
they decided to get married.
She even got a job in Busan.

258
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:30,137
But she suddenly disappeared
for three months.

259
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:33,140
Rin-i was in the UK
to spend time with her mother.

260
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:35,100
But she came back for Eun-o.

261
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,353
In that case,

262
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:40,981
did you go talk to that jerk back then?

263
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,442
We did.

264
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:46,320
But they broke up
as soon as she got to Busan.

265
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:51,492
Oh, right. We went to the hotel
where Eun-o had been hired.

266
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,119
And Rin-i and I

267
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,414
met a woman who had
a job interview with Eun-o.

268
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,918
The hotel decided
not to hire Ms. Lee Eun-o.

269
00:16:02,336 --> 00:16:05,297
I don't think she got the notice.
She came to the hotel.

270
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:09,426
How could a company
cancel her employment so abruptly?

271
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:13,639
So what about my friend?
What happened to her?

272
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:17,643
Did she say she was going somewhere?

273
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:20,896
I don't know.

274
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:23,774
She seemed like a nice girl.

275
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:26,110
We could have been colleagues.

276
00:16:27,277 --> 00:16:28,362
Don't worry.

277
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:32,282
She might have taken the chance
to go on a long trip.

278
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:36,036
Thank you.

279
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,663
She got rid of her phone.

280
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:40,874
We talked about reporting her missing.
It was crazy back then.

281
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,085
Rin-i cried every day.

282
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:49,508
Then, did she tell you where she stayed
when she came back?

283
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:52,094
She wouldn't even tell us
why she broke up with him.

284
00:16:54,888 --> 00:16:56,974
Can't you guess how she must have felt?

285
00:16:57,057 --> 00:16:58,517
Her boyfriend cheated on her.

286
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,937
Her job at the hotel was canceled,
and she had no place to go.

287
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,982
After that, she changed a lot.

288
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:08,652
She used to be innocently kind and quiet.

289
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:12,114
Innocently kind and quiet?

290
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:16,118
Can handing out flyers to random passersby
improve your company's image?

291
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:21,415
I'd like to suggest more direct
and more effective methods.

292
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:24,001
I've brought a few theater posters.

293
00:17:24,084 --> 00:17:27,755
This recent play, <i>How About You?</i>,
is very popular in Daehangno these days.

294
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:29,465
<i>What Do Couples Live for?</i>

295
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,842
will probably be
in the box office for some time.

296
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:34,970
<i>A Good Day for an Affair</i>,
<i>The Taste of Marriage</i>.

297
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,138
All right.

298
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:40,267
Now, find differences
in the posters I'll show you next.

299
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,560
<i>HOW ABOUT YOU?</i>

300
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:46,356
The actress who was just standing
is now holding a bag of <i>ramyeon.</i>

301
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:49,026
The title's meaning became
<i>How About Ramyeon?</i>

302
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:52,071
And in this poster, she's holding a drink.

303
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,782
What do you think?
Don't the products grab your attention?

304
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,284
This doesn't only apply to posters.

305
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:02,372
While the actress is delivering her lines,
she will be holding the bag of <i>ramyeon.</i>

306
00:18:02,956 --> 00:18:06,418
Why? Because she was about to cook it
when her boyfriend came to her house.

307
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,630
Ring, ring. "Who is it?

308
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:14,968
Gosh. What brings you here at this hour?

309
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:17,554
You need to talk to me?
It's three in the morning.

310
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:21,100
{\an8}<i>Ramyeon</i>?
I got hungry when I was about to sleep.

311
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:24,436
Want some <i>ramyeon</i>? It's tasty.

312
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,479
Hold on."

313
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,565
<i>A GOOD DAY FOR AN AFFAIR</i>

314
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:32,236
"By the way, why are you here?
What? You want to break up? Why?

315
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:35,030
You came here to say that at this hour?

316
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:36,323
But why?

317
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:40,119
You've been seeing someone else?
Who? For how long?

318
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:45,040
Put yourself in my shoes.
How can you possibly be okay with this?

319
00:18:45,624 --> 00:18:47,501
How long have you been lying to me?"

320
00:18:48,001 --> 00:18:50,420
Just like this,
during important scenes in the play,

321
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:52,673
she'll deliver her lines
while holding the <i>ramyeon.</i>

322
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:56,510
That's good, but how is that different
from product placement in dramas?

323
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:59,304
I doubt it will increase
our sales that much.

324
00:19:00,764 --> 00:19:04,143
You don't do this for big bucks.
You do it to win people over.

325
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:07,980
"A leading food company
sponsors the culture industry."

326
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:10,899
With this, you can improve
your brand image at the same time.

327
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:13,777
We can easily achieve that
by donating some of our products.

328
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,279
That's another way.

329
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:20,284
But it will be embarrassing
to call a donation "sponsorship."

330
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,369
It probably will be.

331
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:26,707
To be honest, our marketing team
can take care of this.

332
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:30,335
Right. Of course.

333
00:19:30,419 --> 00:19:35,090
But you will definitely be embarrassed
to steal someone else's idea.

334
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,303
It went better than I thought.

335
00:19:39,386 --> 00:19:42,014
Seeing how they reacted,
I can tell they liked your pitch.

336
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:44,933
I always exceed people's expectations.
You can trust me.

337
00:19:48,812 --> 00:19:50,689
Are you holding job interviews today?

338
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:52,900
Yes. We're only recruiting
two people today.

339
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:55,944
But a lot of people applied,
so interviews will last all day.

340
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:58,655
Coffee or green tea?

341
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:01,533
Green tea, please. Thank you.

342
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:12,461
{\an8}-Please read this.
-Okay. Thank you.

343
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:46,453
<i>That day,</i>

344
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:49,873
{\an8}<i>if I hadn't met Yoon Seon-a,</i>

345
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,418
<i>where would I be now?</i>

346
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,427
Everyone, don't be nervous!

347
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:05,806
Just…

348
00:21:05,889 --> 00:21:08,058
Just be yourself.

349
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:11,228
Someone will
definitely recognize your talents.

350
00:21:12,312 --> 00:21:14,690
-Good luck!
-Good luck!

351
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:16,275
Good luck!

352
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,698
-I'll make my own tea.
-Okay.

353
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:25,575
-Jae-won.
-Yes?

354
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:28,036
I'll send Eun-o a request
to join the bidding.

355
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:32,207
She's good at her job.

356
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:34,584
Come on, you saw her portfolio.

357
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:36,461
Oh, right.

358
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:39,381
We're camping out on her rooftop tomorrow.
Do you want to come?

359
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,716
You should come.

360
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:42,884
At Ms. Lee's house?

361
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:45,929
You can just stop by her neighborhood
just like last time.

362
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:46,930
No pressure.

363
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:49,516
And then, you can talk about the project.

364
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:53,979
Camping out on the rooftop in winter?
It's freezing.

365
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:57,357
Come on. Why do you think
<i>naengmyeon </i>is a winter dish?

366
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:59,651
You eat Pyeongyang <i>naengmyeon</i> in winter.

367
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:01,194
It's the same thing.

368
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:04,448
Are you sure I can join you?

369
00:22:04,531 --> 00:22:05,866
Of course.

370
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:08,577
She shares her studio
with her friend, anyway.

371
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:11,830
Remember Geon,
my unemployed novelist friend?

372
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:15,876
Why does she share a house with a man?

373
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:19,046
Did they move in together?

374
00:22:20,088 --> 00:22:22,716
-Are they dating?
-What? No way. They're just friends.

375
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:24,760
-Bundle up. It's cold.
-Okay.

376
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:27,220
See you tomorrow.

377
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:46,198
It's all done.

378
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:53,205
-Is it ready?
-Yes. Almost.

379
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,582
It's burning.

380
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:01,338
Guys, the charcoal's ready.
Let's grill the meat.

381
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:02,506
-Okay.
-Okay.

382
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:04,508
-I'll take them.
-Take these, too.

383
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:08,929
Kyeong-jun, don't tell Eun-o
we ran into Kang Min-su.

384
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:11,890
I'm not stupid.
Why would I? That's an awful memory.

385
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:15,894
She must have been heartbroken.
She doesn't even mention his name.

386
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:18,063
But Eun-o has promise rings.

387
00:23:19,731 --> 00:23:20,899
What?

388
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:26,113
-There are two rings on her necklace.
-No way.

389
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:29,574
You don't think
she's still hung up on Min-su, do you?

390
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:34,621
They broke up because he cheated on her
and knocked up another woman.

391
00:23:34,704 --> 00:23:36,039
She still has the rings?

392
00:23:36,123 --> 00:23:38,583
Then whose rings are they?
They were matching rings.

393
00:23:39,334 --> 00:23:42,087
No way. I doubt they're the ones
she had with Min-su.

394
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,841
She's seeing someone. She must be.

395
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:49,094
Why is she keeping
so many secrets from us now?

396
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:50,929
Listen. She's seeing someone.

397
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:53,431
Did she tell you anything?
You should find out.

398
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:55,475
-Why are you excited?
-That must be it.

399
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:57,102
-Go.
-Bring some drinks.

400
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,272
-Don't tell her anything.
-Okay.

401
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:02,482
Drinks.

402
00:24:04,192 --> 00:24:05,026
Alcohol.

403
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:26,965
It's so cold.

404
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,718
Why is it so cold today?

405
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:38,101
I should have bundled up. Damn it.

406
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:42,689
Am I overdressed for this?

407
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:47,110
Goodness.

408
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:55,160
-Dig in.
-Let's eat.

409
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:56,077
Let's eat.

410
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:57,120
Hold on.

411
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:01,875
Ta-da.

412
00:25:04,252 --> 00:25:08,506
Let me tell you about this liquor
before we start our meal.

413
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:10,383
-Just pour it.
-Let's just drink.

414
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:11,343
Let's just drink it.

415
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:17,098
You'll regret it.
Let me tell you about this liquor.

416
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:21,186
This beautiful liquor was made by mixing
1,200 types of centuries-old extracts.

417
00:25:21,978 --> 00:25:23,688
Do you know how much I paid for it?

418
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:26,316
-I paid 100,000 won.
-From whom?

419
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:29,903
From these two fools!

420
00:25:30,570 --> 00:25:31,947
How much is it, then?

421
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:35,200
A bottle would cost
about three million won.

422
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:38,161
Come here. You jerk, come back.

423
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:39,537
You scammer.

424
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:41,331
-Give it back.
-Hey.

425
00:25:41,414 --> 00:25:43,875
-Where did you get that expensive bottle?
-Give it.

426
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:47,879
-From my cousin.
-From Jae-won.

427
00:25:48,797 --> 00:25:51,967
My cousin got totally messed up
because of some girl lately.

428
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,010
He almost became an alcoholic.

429
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:56,513
You know, the camera thief.

430
00:25:58,181 --> 00:25:59,599
What a romantic.

431
00:25:59,683 --> 00:26:02,602
He went to the police station to find her
when he got wasted.

432
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:06,356
So, Kyeong-jun took
all of his liquor from his house.

433
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:08,942
-He sold it to me.
-Only for 100,000 won.

434
00:26:09,442 --> 00:26:11,569
If this one costs three million won…

435
00:26:12,904 --> 00:26:15,323
-How much would the other ones cost?
-You scammer.

436
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:19,953
Eun-o, I'll let you taste it first.

437
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:24,165
You jerk.

438
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:27,127
If it was that expensive,
you should have told me.

439
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:29,587
-You're so vicious.
-Did you call me a jerk?

440
00:26:29,671 --> 00:26:30,839
Yes. You scamming jerk.

441
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:33,550
-My Rin-i, do you want some?
-Hey, hold on.

442
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:35,844
Don't call her "my Rin-i."

443
00:26:35,927 --> 00:26:38,763
Only I can call her "my Rin-i."

444
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,851
Kyeong-jun's Rin-i.
Let me pour you a drink.

445
00:26:45,312 --> 00:26:46,730
-You dropped some!
-Come on.

446
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:51,651
JAE-WON

447
00:26:53,028 --> 00:26:54,779
Can you even taste this?

448
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:56,072
Hey, where are you?

449
00:26:57,532 --> 00:26:59,034
You're here? Hold on.

450
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:03,580
Hey, over here. Come up here.

451
00:27:03,663 --> 00:27:04,914
-Okay.
-Is that Jae-won?

452
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:07,208
I forgot to tell you.

453
00:27:07,292 --> 00:27:09,044
I invited him here. I hope it's okay.

454
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:10,879
-Should I hide this?
-Take the stairs.

455
00:27:16,426 --> 00:27:17,469
Jae-won!

456
00:27:21,681 --> 00:27:23,516
Come. Join us. We just started.

457
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:26,770
It's your first time meeting my friends.
Say hello.

458
00:27:27,270 --> 00:27:28,730
Hello, I'm Kang Geon.

459
00:27:30,231 --> 00:27:32,150
I'm Park Jae-won.

460
00:27:32,734 --> 00:27:34,944
-You're handsome.
-I've been wanting to meet you.

461
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:39,908
This is my friend, Jae-won.

462
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:52,545
It's nice to meet you. I'm Park Jae-won.

463
00:27:58,134 --> 00:27:58,968
Hi.

464
00:28:04,099 --> 00:28:06,643
I was very curious about you,
Ms. Lee Eun-o.

465
00:28:12,023 --> 00:28:13,900
That's long enough for a handshake.

466
00:28:13,983 --> 00:28:16,111
-Give me what you brought.
-Here.

467
00:28:17,404 --> 00:28:20,657
What? You took off your ring?
Where did it go?

468
00:28:21,282 --> 00:28:22,409
Oh, the ring?

469
00:28:23,576 --> 00:28:24,869
I threw it out.

470
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,794
Because everything about her was fake.

471
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:55,275
Geon, pour him a glass, too.

472
00:28:55,358 --> 00:28:57,777
Okay. I'll go bring a glass.

473
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:04,409
-Jae-won, sit down.
-Okay. Thanks.

474
00:29:04,492 --> 00:29:05,952
Sit down, Jae-won.

475
00:29:09,372 --> 00:29:11,791
You must be freezing.
You should have layered up more.

476
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:14,335
It's not that cold. I'm okay.

477
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:15,712
-Did you drive here?
-Yes.

478
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:17,797
You should call a chauffeur.

479
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:22,594
-Isn't it pretty here?
-It's nice.

480
00:29:25,388 --> 00:29:28,391
-Eun-o, are you okay?
-What?

481
